sql:
SELECT ci.item_description, ci.source_url, pt.template_name
FROM content_items AS ci
JOIN permission_templates AS pt ON ci.usage_purpose = pt.template_name;

SELECT ci.item_id, ci.item_description, ci.content_type_id, ci.usage_purpose, ci.file_extension, ci.source_url
FROM content_items ci
JOIN content_types ct ON ci.content_type_id = ct.type_id;

external_knowledge:
- In the metaphor used, 'oceanic currents' represent different categories of content, in this case, filtering to 'Video'.;
- 'Visual waves' symbolize the video content items.;
- 'Average weight' refers to the average file size of the video content.;
- The '3Lau Social Media' ocean is the specified project.;
- 'Groups of more than three' means only consider content types where there are more than three content items.;

sql:
SELECT * 
FROM content_usages
WHERE usage_type = 'commercial';

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM content_items
WHERE source_id NOT IN (SELECT source_id FROM content_sources);

SELECT COUNT(item_id)
FROM content_items
WHERE file_size > 1000000;

SELECT ci.item_description, ci.source_url, p.contact_email
FROM content_items ci
RIGHT JOIN permissions p ON ci.item_id = p.item_id;

SELECT item_id 
FROM content_usages 
WHERE project_id = (SELECT MAX(project_id) FROM projects);

external_knowledge:
- 'Voyagers' refers to users accessing content; 
- 'Exploring the depths of personal content' means accessing items for personal use; 
- 'Treasures' metaphorically represent the content items; 
- 'Exploration permits' symbolize permission requests;
- 'Current status of their exploration permits' refers to the status of the permission request for the content access.
